```go
package main

import (
	"github.com/huaweicloud/pulumi-huaweicloud/sdk/go/huaweicloud/Waf"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-huaweicloud/sdk/go/huaweicloud/Waf"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi/sdk/v3/go/pulumi"
)

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		certificate1, err := Waf.GetCertificate(ctx, &waf.GetCertificateArgs{
			Name: "certificate name",
		}, nil)
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		_, err = Waf.NewDomain(ctx, "domain1", &Waf.DomainArgs{
			Domain:          pulumi.String("www.domainname.com"),
			CertificateId:   pulumi.String(certificate1.Id),
			CertificateName: pulumi.String(certificate1.Name),
			KeepPolicy:      pulumi.Bool(false),
			Proxy:           pulumi.Bool(false),
			Servers: waf.DomainServerArray{
				&waf.DomainServerArgs{
					ClientProtocol: pulumi.String("HTTPS"),
					ServerProtocol: pulumi.String("HTTP"),
					Address:        pulumi.String("192.168.10.1"),
					Port:           pulumi.Int(8080),
				},
			},
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}
```

```java
package generated_program;

import com.pulumi.Context;
import com.pulumi.Pulumi;
import com.pulumi.core.Output;
import com.pulumi.huaweicloud.Waf.WafFunctions;
import com.pulumi.huaweicloud.DedicatedElb.inputs.GetCertificateArgs;
import com.pulumi.huaweicloud.Waf.Domain;
import com.pulumi.huaweicloud.Waf.DomainArgs;
import com.pulumi.huaweicloud.Waf.inputs.DomainServerArgs;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.Map;
import java.io.File;
import java.nio.file.Files;
import java.nio.file.Paths;

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Pulumi.run(App::stack);
    }

    public static void stack(Context ctx) {
        final var certificate1 = WafFunctions.getCertificate(GetCertificateArgs.builder()
            .name("certificate name")
            .build());

        var domain1 = new Domain("domain1", DomainArgs.builder()        
            .domain("www.domainname.com")
            .certificateId(certificate1.applyValue(getCertificateResult -> getCertificateResult.id()))
            .certificateName(certificate1.applyValue(getCertificateResult -> getCertificateResult.name()))
            .keepPolicy(false)
            .proxy(false)
            .servers(DomainServerArgs.builder()
                .clientProtocol("HTTPS")
                .serverProtocol("HTTP")
                .address("192.168.10.1")
                .port(8080)
                .build())
            .build());

}
```
